    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This shouldn't be necessary. Regardless of whether you are behind a NAT or not, you should be able to connect to any peer who has their ports open. \r\n\r\nI think this may have occurred whilst the main peers were struggling with disk space (due to another crash) and were not responding to your RPC requests. \r\n\r\nIn the future, you don't need to port forward these ports, although it is required if you want other peers to discover and connect to your node. ",
